column5: Hey guys I heard jumbo perch are biting ing cooks bay right now. Can anyone confirm this ?

This time of year all the perch move out of Cook's Bay and head for the narrow's in Orillia. The real big jumbo's hide under the    bridge there. Any muskie size crankbait will do the trick.  Good luck  And BTW welcome aboard
I herd that wast true !!!1!! also.  Keep it on the down low, even so.
Went to the Barrie docks on Saturday, and caught absolutly nothing....very weird!
my friend went to barrie docks on sunday and got 3 little ones, then he stopped by lefroy and did very well, even got few jumbos.
Thanks guys I think im gonna try barrie on saturday. Ill post my results
Nothin weird about that    That place can be very hit or miss sometimes.
